<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 5:22PM CST  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Garvin,
south central Cleveland and south central McClain Counties through
545 PM CST...
At 522 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Lindsay, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Purcell, Slaughterville, Lindsay, Lexington, Maysville, Wayne,
Rosedale, Erin Springs and Payne.
This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 79 and 97.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
